"title": "5527: shield",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5527",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A piece of armour used to fend off blows or missiles such as arrows. God is described as the shield of his people; protecting, giving help, strength and favour. Faith is the shield with which believers are to ward off spiritual attack.</p>\n<h2>Shields are pieces of armour</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:11-2Chr11:12\">2CH 11:11–11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:5\">2CH 32:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:16\">NEH 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:5\">NAM 2:5</a> <em>A number of shields were used to make a wall of defence.</em></p>\n<h2>Kinds of shield</h2>\n<h3>Large and small shields</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:3\">JER 46:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:16-1Kgs10:17\">1KI 10:16–10:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:15-2Chr9:16\">2CH 9:15–9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:8\">2CH 14:8</a></p>\n<h3>Gold shields</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:7\">2SA 8:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:7\">1CH 18:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:16-1Kgs10:17\">1KI 10:16–10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:26\">1KI 14:26</a></p>\n<h3>Bronze shields</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:27\">1KI 14:27</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Shields made of combustible materials</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:9\">EZK 39:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Shields covered with leather</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:5\">ISA 21:5</a></strong> <em>Leather shields were rubbed with oil to preserve them and to deflect blows from swords or arrows.</em></p>\n<h2>Shields in warfare</h2>\n<h3>As part of an army's equipment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:8\">2CH 14:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:23-1Chr12:24\">1CH 12:23–12:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:12\">2CH 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:14\">2CH 26:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:16\">NEH 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Their use in battle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:18\">1CH 5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:7\">1SA 17:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:32\">2KI 19:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:3\">JER 46:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:9\">JER 46:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:11\">JER 51:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:24\">EZK 23:24</a></p>\n<h2>The figurative use of shields</h2>\n<h3>God is called a shield of his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1\">GEN 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:10\">PSA 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2\">PSA 18:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:7\">PRO 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>God acts as a shield</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:19-Exod14:20\">EXO 14:19–14:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:12\">ISA 52:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:8\">ISA 58:8</a></p>\n<h3>God protects his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:5\">ISA 31:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:3\">PSA 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:7\">PSA 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:10\">PSA 32:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:2\">PSA 125:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:7\">PSA 140:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:5\">ZEC 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:8\">ZEC 12:8</a></p>\n<h3>God is a refuge for his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:2\">PSA 144:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:30\">PSA 18:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:114\">PSA 119:114</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:5\">PRO 30:5</a></p>\n<h3>God is the help and strength of his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:7\">PSA 28:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:29\">DEU 33:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:20\">PSA 33:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:9-Ps115:11\">PSA 115:9–115:11</a></p>\n<h3>God gives victory to his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:36\">2SA 22:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:35\">PSA 18:35</a></p>\n<h3>God's favour is compared to a shield</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:12\">PSA 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:3\">PSA 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:10\">PSA 32:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:9-Ps84:11\">PSA 84:9–84:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's faithfulness is compared to a shield</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:4\">PSA 91:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A shield is used as a picture of defiance towards God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:25-Job15:26\">JOB 15:25–15:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Faith is given to the believer to act as a shield</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:16\">EPH 6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:5\">1PE 1:5</a></p>",
